Relbeek-<br>
      the same goes for you.  You seem to have an attitude that people would give a @#%$ about what sort of supposed &quot;vengeance&quot; you could muster if a guild drove the server to ffa.  Hearing you bark like that is enough to make me want to level an alt to the point of being in a position to actively and publicly form a guild with the SOLE GOAL OF AN FFA ATTITUDE.  You just don't get it do ya??  It only takes ONE guild to crack the system.  Not 15%, not 5% hell probably less than .1% of the server.  Frankly, the thought of ffa is rather distasteful, but not as much so as your attitude.  I have been plenty patient and non greedy.  You can look at my gear for my level and confirm it.  But when I hear you insinuate that because I do desire to complete my epic now or hell even soon for that matter, I am greedy, I see red.  I have been waiting to COMPLETE my epic for as long as some mages have started their characters, leveled them AND completed their epics.  This is wrong.  I HAVE played by the rules.  The rules WILL change... or someone WILL come along to change them.  Bank on it bucko.<br>
<br>
